 training opportunities that create awareness, understanding, and inclusion of all gender and sexual identities represented within the UNT community. - Ally Training, Intimate Partner Violence in LGBT Communities, National Coming Out Day Engagement and Involvement: Serving the UNT community through partnerships with campus and community organizations and promoting policies and practices that are inclusive of all gender and sexual identities. - Dallas Pride Parade, Outrageous Oral History, Transgender Day of Remembrance Student Success and Leadership Development: Fostering an environment that affirms and celebrates all gender and sexual identities and providing opportunities for personal growth through dialogue, exploring the intersections of identity, and creating support systems to enable achievement. - Diversity and Inclusion Career Fair, Lavender Graduation, OUTFits Clothing Closet About Us Programs & Services Resources Education & Training Events Get Involved Alumni Opportunities & Giving Contact Us Visit Us Hurley Administration Bldg 1501 W. Chestnut Denton, Texas 76203-5107 Mail Us University of North Texas Division of Institutional Equity and Diversity 1155 Union Circle #310937 Denton, TX 76203 Contact Us 940-565-2711 Equity.Diversity@unt.edu Technical issues? Site last updated on May 09, 2017 Disclaimer| AA/EOE/ADA| Privacy| Electronic Accessibility| State of Texas Online| Emergency Preparedness| THECB Online Resume System Student Consumer Information| UNT Compliance Hotline| Governors Committee on People with Disabilities| Texas Veterans Portal| UNT Home Site last updated on May 09, 2017 | Important Links 